segment.source: After you sequence an application and before you save it, you can use the Change History tab to view the historical information about a sequenced application package.
segment.target: After you sequence an application and before you save it, you can use the Change History tab to view the historical information about a sequenced application package.

segment.source: This tab is read only and cannot be modified.
segment.target: This tab is read only and cannot be modified.

segment.source: The date a sequenced application package was modified.
segment.target: The date a sequenced application package was modified.

segment.source: The GUID for the version of the sequenced application package that is loaded, which can be used during deployment to specify a particular version of the package.
segment.target: The GUID for the version of the sequenced application package that is loaded, which can be used during deployment to specify a particular version of the package.

segment.source: This section of the Change History tab displays specific information about the Application Virtualization Sequencer (the Sequencer) that was used to create the sequenced application package.
segment.target: This section of the Change History tab displays specific information about the Application Virtualization Sequencer (the Sequencer) that was used to create the sequenced application package.

segment.source: The version of the Sequencer used to create the package.
segment.target: The version of the Sequencer used to create the package.

segment.source: The name of the sequencing engineer.
segment.target: The name of the sequencing engineer.

segment.source: The sequencing computer used to create the sequenced application package.
segment.target: The sequencing computer used to create the sequenced application package.

segment.source: Indicates whether the sequenced application package was upgraded and saved.
segment.target: Indicates whether the sequenced application package was upgraded and saved.

segment.source: Indicates the method used to save the application package.
segment.target: Indicates the method used to save the application package.

segment.source: The version of Windows used to create a sequenced application package.
segment.target: The version of Windows used to create a sequenced application package.

segment.source: The path on the Sequencing computer of its System folder.
segment.target: The path on the Sequencing computer of its System folder.

segment.source: The location on the sequencing computer of its Windows folder.
segment.target: The location on the sequencing computer of its Windows folder.

segment.source: The location on the sequencing computer of its User folder.
segment.target: The location on the sequencing computer of its User folder.

segment.source: The type of operating system on the sequencing computer.
segment.target: The type of operating system on the sequencing computer.

segment.source: The processor of the sequencing computer system.
segment.target: The processor of the sequencing computer system.

segment.source: Indicates whether or not the sequencing computer's most recent boot-up was normal.
segment.target: Indicates whether or not the sequencing computer's most recent boot-up was normal.

segment.source: Indicates whether Terminal Services are operant on the sequencing computer system.
segment.target: Indicates whether Terminal Services are operant on the sequencing computer system.

segment.source: Indicates whether Remote Desktop is operant on the sequencing computer.
segment.target: Indicates whether Remote Desktop is operant on the sequencing computer.

segment.source: Indicates the availability of any version of the .NET Framework on the sequencing computer.
segment.target: Indicates the availability of any version of the .NET Framework on the sequencing computer.

segment.source: Indicates the availability of any version of Internet Explorer on the sequencing computer.
segment.target: Indicates the availability of any version of Internet Explorer on the sequencing computer.

segment.source: Indicates the availability of any version of Windows Media Player on the sequencing computer.
segment.target: Indicates the availability of any version of Windows Media Player on the sequencing computer.
